To describe the power dependence of the luminescence thermal quenching a rate model is proposed that will explicitly take into account the filling of localised states28,51. It is considered that carriers are able to radiatively recombine from the LDOS that exists within the band-gap. The distribution can be made up of both single and double Gaussian components, following the observation for GaAsBi in27, and is given by;7gLDOS=N0[(1−y)⋅gGauss(E,EMob,σ1)+y⋅gGauss(E,EOff,σ2)]\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
